System.out.println(bufferedReader.readLine());
I am of course closing all the resources, I wrote this code only to visualize the problem. That prints 123 but it is supposed to print 1. How can I fix that?

Please using this api: BufferedReader.readLine.
Answer:<<<api>>>: BufferedReader.readLine
<<<code>>>: try { System.out.println(bufferedReader.readLine()); } catch (Exception e) { e.printStackTrace(); }
<<<explanation>>>: The BufferedReader.readLine() method reads a line of text. It returns null if the stream has reached the end. If you are seeing 123, it means that the BufferedReader is reading all the data from the stream. If you want to read only the first line, you should call readLine() only once.
